Don't Believe The Hype. "Products not worth the hype" are quite divisive here in the beauty community; some people think that just because one person doesn't feel an item lived up to its internet hype that they're attacking them and their own love for that specific product. Of course, this absolutely isn't the case and no one should get butt-hurt over someone not liking something. If any of these products mentioned are your number 1 forever and always then that's great - I'm jealous! And I'm pretty sure there's plenty of products out there that I love and others don't. That's the beauty of being an adult, isn't it?Either way, I'm here to share with you guys today some products that I feel get a lot of love from the beauty community in blogs and videos, and from my friends included (hence why I purchased them!) but unfortunately for some reason or another, they fell short of my expectations. I want to make it clear that not all of these are necessarily bad products (there are some downright crap ones, and I'll get to those)... some of these I do use quite often, but it's just that they didn't live up to the crazy mega fan girl hype they have online. I've included quite a lot of higher end products, mostly found in the likes of Sephora. I feel like high-end products get hyped up a lot more and with good reason; typically a more expensive product will or at least should perform better although this is obviously not always the case as you soon see when you try a range of different products. I'm generally very picky and harsher a critic on more expensive products because they should be out-performing their cheaper dupes for the price. Not to say that these are the worst products in the world, or to put you off looking into all of them, it's just to say that actually what was supposed to be the mecca of all lipsticks turned out to be the meh of all lipsticks, for me at least. Let's start off with skincare. I've mentioned this in empties posts before, the Garnier Micellar Water. Why is it in here if I've gone through bottles and bottles of it, you ask? Because it's convenient and I can easily take my makeup off with this and cotton pads instead of having to wash a face cloth every night from an oil cleanse. I don't love it, I don't think it does anything particularly nice for my skin and it doesn't take makeup off in the best way so I do have to rely on a good cleanser afterwards. I do use it and repurchase it, but it's sitting pretty in this post because I just don't feel like it's as amazing as everyone on YouTube makes it out to be. SUE ME.I remember seeing this in every favourites or hair related post a few years ago and decided to invest once I got my extensions out a few years ago. This Macadamia Oil Deep Repair Mask is so mediocre it hurts. I didn't find it made my hair feel any less frizzy or tangle-free, it did nothing for split ends or damage. Sure, it made it a bit shinier but I could get that with most masks or shine sprays if I really wanted to. I had such high hopes for this, maybe a bit too high - but I think anyone who remembers the hype around this will agree that it was biiiiig. It was another case of just using it up because I felt like I wanted to finish it, but I've always kind of resented this because it was so expensive and never worked for me. I'll stick to my Schwarzkopf for salon priced products, thank you xoxoI'm really crap with my nails and don't tend to fall into much hype with polishes. I actually don't think that there is a lot of hype around brands or shades except for maybe Essie and OPI. I remember when Formula X was launched by Sephora, everyone and their mother was talking about how incredible the formula, finishes, shades and lasting power was. I was delighted to see them pop up in a French Sephora a few months later and decided to give a lilac one a go. I hated it. It was streaky, chipped after a day and didn't even dry nicely in the first place. I've tried it with/without different base and top coats and have come to the conclusion that Formula X just isn't for me. I also bought a glittery shade in a Sephora sale a few months ago just to give it another go. I certainly prefer the glitter shade to the creamy lilac one, but overall I just don't think they're the end all be all of polishes and don't think they're worth the hype behind them.The Bite Beauty Agave Lip Mask was one of the things at the top of my Sephora list when my mother went to Canada. I had heard how this thick mask would make my lips feel brand new by morning. I suffer from really bad cracked and flaky lips so I was all about something that would be super moisturizing and hydrating. This is not it. I should preface by saying that the woman at Sephora accidentally gave my mother a tinted version, so I'm not sure if that has affected the performance of the product (I don't think it should be any less hydrating though). Regardless, this stuff is so crap and not worth the money at all. It's very sticky and thick, which I would be okay with using at night if it meant that my lips felt super moisturized come morning but that's just not the case. I don't notice any difference in the condition of my lips between using this or something like a heft dollop of Carmex. Once the thickness of the Bite mask wears off the dryness in my lips sets right back in. Boo-urns. I'm really just using it up at this stage.Continuing on with lips; the Kat Von D Liquid Lipsticks. This will probably be a bit of a shock to most people, because they get so much love on Instagram and elsewhere online. In its defense, the only one I've tried that I'm not mad about is Vampira, a deep vampy red. Since buying this I have heard that the darker shades don't perform as well as the others, so this might be something to do with it and I have some more nude shades that I like much more. I found this to be kind of patchy and uneven in places on the lips, I definitely need a lipliner underneath to disguise any areas that the liquid li

How I Dye and Style My Hair Without a doubt the thing I get asked most about is my hair, about both the style and the colour. I realised the other day that I'd never really done a post about how I do my hair on a day to day basis and although my hair is naturally wavy, there are certain products and tools that I go back to time and time again.The Colour I'll start with the thing I get asked most often about - the colour of my hair. I dyed my hair to a darker, coppery colour from blonde around two years ago but I struggled to get it the exact colour I wanted. I was using semi-permanent colours that were kind of coppery brown but they faded so fast it was almost pointless and they only gave my brown hair a tinge of copper anyway. I did this for around a year and tried so many different shades and dyes but nothing worked the way I wanted so I accepted that this wasn't going to be a home dye job.I went to my hairdressers (Lush Hair and Beauty in Bishop Auckland if any readers are local to me!) and my hairdresser told me that there was no way I'd get the fiery shade I wanted without either bleaching my hair or stripping the colour from it which was something I'd been expecting anyway. I went for latter option as it's much better for your hair and although the treatment can be pricier than your average hair salon visit, it is worth it if you're wanting a colour like this. Kirsty put the treatment on my hair, stripped all of the colour from it and got my hair the exact vibrant colour I wanted so if this is a colour you want, I would definitely recommend a salon visit to begin with. I went back twice more to get the colour re-done so that it stayed vibrant but since then I've been doing it myself at home and have found my holy grail of home hair dye.I'd heard really good things about the Schwarzkopf Live XXL hair dye anyway for those who want bright hair colours especially so when I came across the shade Mango in my local Boots store by chance, I thought I'd give it a try. Since then I've never used any other colour on my hair. It's a bright bright copper colour that is truly orange rather than red (which I struggled with at first - so many copper colours have reddish tones!) and it lasts for so much longer than other dyes I've used. Of course, with copper being a bright colour it does fade and that's inevitable but this is long lasting for such a vibrant shade. I dye my hair every 3-4 weeks but could probably get away with going longer if need be. It is honestly my holy grail hair product.The WashWhen it comes to washing my hair, I don't really have a holy grail conditioner as such but a few months ago I discovered this beauty of a shampoo and now I couldn't go without it. This Curly Wurly Coconut Shampoo is from Lush Cosmetics. Up until maybe late last year, I hadn't properly ventured properly into Lush's haircare section and had only tried the Salt Spray but I'm so glad I picked this little pot up. The shampoo isn't like anything I've ever used before and has a thick, paste-type texture with lots of oils and coconut pieces to really nourish the hair and although it does do just that, I love this shampoo because of the finish it gives my hair. As soon as you rinse this off you can feel your hair just getting a bit bouncier and it gives it a really lovely "big" texture, defining the waves in my hair and making them more beachy. I don't use it every time I wash my hair and only do use it when I want that really big, textured, summer hair but it's such a great product for styling and getting the bed head look I sport on almost a daily basis.The StyleThese next two products are both from The Bardou and are what I use to style my hair and they are honestly so great. The Immaculate Spray Dry Shampoo is one of my favourite things in my haircare box at the minute and for good reason. I know we all know how great dry shampoo is (umm, goodbye greasy roots) but this one is on another level for me. It doesn't leave that white, powdery residue behind so doesn't make you look like you're going grey but still manages to mattify the roots, something which is essential when styling a messy full fringe like mine. I also use this even when I've washed my hair because it gives great volume and I feel like it stops my wavy hair going frizzy and flyaway throughout the day too so it really is another of my holy grails. I just spray it on my roots and my fringe, get my fingertips and really rough it up!The second one is the Finishing Mist Hairspray. I've had a bit of a rocky relationship with hairspray as a whole for the last couple of years as I used to have such an nightmare finding one that didn't just make my waves either dry as sticks or as a sticky as if I'd covered them in maple syrup. This one reignited my love for hairspray and has been a staple ever since. Because it's not as heavy as traditional hairspray it doesn't drag my hair down so I just spray this in little squirts all over my hair and rough up the whole thing, adding more where I need it. It stops my bedhead look from dropping out throughout the day!Also, The Bardou do lots of different hair products whether you want bed hair like me or a really sleek and sophisticated look and you can get 10% off at the already affordable prices using the code SALTANDCHIC10 :)As for the hair tools, my ghd marine allure stylers are all I need. I use them every day to style my fringe and to tame the ends of my hair and on the days where my natural hair is looking a little bit meh, I use it just to add a few loose waves. As my hair is still on the short side, I find that it's easier to curl with straighteners rather than actual curling tongs or wands. They're just the right thickness to give you loose waves instead of the spaghetti type curls!So that's how I do my hair! If you have any more questions about do leave me a comment or tweet me @saltandchic - hope you enjoyed the post!Amy x*THIS POST CONTAINS PR SAMPLES

7 One-Minute-Miracle Products Our Moms Put to the Test We had some of our editors ask their own moms to take a few of the latest beauty wonders for a spin and report back on the results.

Who
Sandra Vieira
Age
52
Mom To
Jillian Vieira, Fashion Editor
Early Beauty Lessons
“My mom would always say, ‘Make sure you wash your face and don’t forget your ears! You may have potatoes growing behind there.’”
The Product
Elizabeth Arden Prevage Anti-Aging Antioxidant Infused Essence, $120, thebay.com 
Her Verdict
“It was refreshing, absorbed immediately and didn’t take any time to apply since it only adds a simple step between cleansing and moisturizing. A little goes a long way. I’ve noticed a huge change: within two days my face was softer and smoother and those little lines seem to be less defined.”

Who
Judith Hume
Age
Undisclosed
Mom To
Veronica Saroli, Assistant Editor
Early Beauty Lessons
“The best beauty advice I received was from my grandmother who said, ‘Always wash and use a cream’ (I believe Ponds was a favourite) and ‘Never give your age!’ In fact, when she died, it was in the first paragraph of her will that her age was not to go in the paper.”
The Product
Jouviance InjectFX, $35, jouviance.com
Her Verdict
“This ‘simulated filler’ has a bit of a tint and felt like a non-greasy, creamy cover up. I liked that it blended into my skin easily, so it wasn’t noticeable. I wanted it to treat the lines around my lips, and although there was no drastic improvement, it did help

Who
Julie deCarufel
Age
64
Mom To
Laura deCarufel, Editor-in-Chief
Early Beauty Lessons
“My mother would say, ‘Don’t use soap on your face.’ She seldom wore makeup. I followed her example and didn’t wear any makeup until my mid-twenties.”
The Product
Sealuxe Ritual Rose Elegant Bath Tea, $12, kissandmakeupstore.com
Her Verdict
“I love beautiful-smelling soaps for my bath and shower. This felt good for my achy muscles after exercise and was soft on my skin. The salt in it dissolved very quickly. The part I liked the best was the rose scent.”

Who
Christina Begy
Age
59
Mom To
Evie Begy, Marketing Manager
Pet Peeve
“I have a thing about feet. I can’t stand seeing a super-chic woman who blows it all with rough, cracked heels. That’s like sweeping dust bunnies under the rug, but forgetting to roll the rug back again.”
The Product
CND Cucumber Heel Therapy Intensive Treatment, $50, salons
Her Verdict
“I was surprised by the substantial texture: It’s more like crème brûlée than the whipped cream I was expecting. It took a while to rub in and absorb. Amazing: a self-administered foot massage! It smelled great. My feet were silky smooth immediately. The small cracks were visibly improved after one use, and by the end of the week they were gone. Can I try it on my husband?”

Who
Barbara Yvonne Hotson
Age
69
Mom To
Jessica Hotson, Creative Director
Beauty Habits
“I still have fairly thick hair, but as I get older, it often looks dry and tired. I use hair masks and sometimes I’ll wrap my head in a plastic bag to add heat—a very attractive look, according to my husband. Sometimes I’ll leave them on for an afternoon while I cut the grass.”
The Product
Schwarzkopf Essence Ultimate Amber + Oil Nutrition 60 Second Treatment, $13, Rexall
Her Verdict
“It had almost a whipped texture—it went on very creamy and rinsed out clean. After the treatment, I could comb my hair easily and run my fingers through with no tangles—as if I’d had a trim to get rid of all the split ends. I colour my hair three times a year to hide the grey and this treatment made my hair soft and silky, like it feels after a dye job. I’ll definitely use it again, and my husband will not miss the bag on my head.”

Who
Shawna Ostroff
Age
13.89 (in Celsius)
Mom To
Carly Ostroff, Assistant Digital Editor
Beauty Habits
“When I was younger, it was all about having a minimal regimen. Now, I take more time in the morning to achieve that ‘effortless’ look. I call it ‘the works:’ moisturizer, foundation, eyebrow pencil, eyeshadow, eyeliner, blush and lipstick.”
The Product
Charlotte Tilbury Instant Look in a Palette, $85, holtrenfrew.com 
Her Verdict
“I need a GPS for my car and a GPS for my face to navigate the sheer number of beauty products I’ve collected, and to tell me which one to use where and how. This palette is the perfect tool to streamline my routine and has taken the guesswork out of makeup application (especially before I’ve had my coffee) because it comes with directions. It has everything I need to be ready in five minutes. The overall look is me, but better—and dare I say it, younger.”

Who
Roma Sheen
Age
65
Mom To
Rani Sheen, Beauty Editor
Splurge Strategy
“I definitely spend money on moisturizer and more recently on exfoliators and serums (thanks to my beauty editor daughter).”
The Product
Tata Harper Boosted Contouring Eye Mask, $211, murale.ca
Her Verdict
“The best thing by far was the smell. It smelled divine, like wild English flowers in the spring. The unexpected thing was that I noticed a difference after the first use—smoother and softer skin around my eyes. It said not to use water to remove it, so I wiped it off with a cleansing cloth.”
For the latest in fashion and beauty, pick up a copy of The Kit’s print edition found inside The Toronto Star on Thursdays, Edmonton Journal, Calgary Herald and Ottawa Citizen on Fridays and The Vancouver Sun and Montreal Gazette on Saturdays.
In Toronto, look for The Kit Compact, our monthly beauty and style pop-up mag, the first week of every month.

Scrapbook #JennyJenny no21 Μεγάλη Δευτέρα σήμερα και υποθέτω ότι νιώθετε κι εσείς σαν κι εμένα. Ένα αίσθημα προσμονής για λίγη ξεκούραση και μερικές βόλτες στον ήλιο, που ευχόμαστε όλοι να μας συντροφεύσει και τις επόμενες μέρες.

#nature Στο σπίτι του Jenny Jenny έχουμε την ευκαιρία να απολαμβάνουμε τη φύση, ειδικά τις τελευταίες μέρες που ο καιρός είναι καλός. Μπορεί να μην έχουμε το χρόνο να χαθούμε στο πράσινο αλλά και μόνο η θέα του αρκεί. Αν μείνετε Αθήνα το Πάσχα, βρείτε όμορφα μέρη για πεζοπορία ή περίπατο για αναζωογόνηση.

#mygirls Και για του λόγου του αληθές, δείτε πόσο όμορφα μπορεί να περνάει κανείς στη δουλειά του. Η Αμαλία και Ελιάνα απολαμβάνουν τον όμορφο καιρό στον πράσινο κήπο του σπιτιού του Jenny Jenny.

#hope Το νέο ανοιξιάτικο τεύχος του HOPE είναι πλέον διαθέσιμο στο App Store για να το κατεβάσετε εντελώς δωρεάν. Πολύχρωμο, χαρούμενο, αισιόδοξο και ελπιδοφόρο είναι ότι χρειάζεστε για να ενημερωθείτε για τις νέες τάσεις σε μόδα και ομορφιά αλλά και για να γνωρίσετε ενδιαφέρουσες προσωπικότητες. Το μήνυμα του HOPE ταιριάζει απόλυτα με το moto που έχει πάνω της η καινούργια μου ξύλινη θήκη για το κινητό Mouchmouch designs που βρήκα στο jyou.gr 

#haircolors Ξεφυλλίζοντας τις διαδικτυακές σελίδες του ανοιξιάτικου HOPE έπεσα πάνω στο θέμα με τα haircolor trends που θα κυριαρχήσουν αυτή τη σεζόν. Ανακάλυψα ότι και το 8.4 από την Keratin Color του Schwarzkopf έχει μία θέση σε αυτές.

#myhair Ανακαλύψτε κι εσείς τη δική σας αγαπημένη απόχρωση από την πρώτη μόνιμη περιποιητική βαφή με κερατίνη και μην ξεχάσετε να πάρετε μέρος στο διαγωνισμό του Jenny.gr. Δύο τυχερές θα έχουν την ευκαιρία να αποκτήσουν το αγαπημένο τους χρώμα από την Keratin Color του Schwarzkopf για 6 ολόκληρους μήνες.

#guests Αυτό το Σαββατοκύριακο στο σπίτι του Jenny Jenny υποδεχθήκαμε την Βίκυ Σταυροπούλου και τον καλό της φίλο Ιβάν Σβιτάιλο, ο οποίος της έκανε έκπληξη. Glamour Bag май (фото и обзор) Для бьюти-блогера редкий солнечный день в Петербурге, это не только «Вау! Как здорово! Пойду погуляю!», это еще и возможность сделать сочные кадры. Поэтому, увидев сегодня утром за окном солнце, я решила совместить приятное с полезным — погулять по залитому солнцем городу и пофоткать состав майской косметички Glamour Bag, чтобы показать его вам :))1. Этот выпуск посвящен выпускному и, хотя для меня это событие уже давно не актуально, я нашла в составе кое-что интересное и для себя :))2. Матовый лак для ногтей с гелевым эффектом Lumene. Производитель обещает ультра-блестящее покрытие без полос и сколов. Проверить его обещания предстоит моей племяшке, для которой тема выпускного как раз актуальна :))3. Тушь «Искусство Объема» от Faberlic.Новая фибровая кисть большого размера обещает нам мгновенный объем без комочков.4. Тушь для бровей от Divage.Цветной гель для моделирования бровей со специальной щеточкой для укладки бровей :)) В составе: витамин Е и алоэ вера, благодаря которым тушь обладает увлажняющим и смягчающим эффектом.5. Жидкая матовая помада Maybelline Vivid Matte Lipstick яркого ягодного оттенка. Барби бы одобрила :))Свотч на руке долго оттирала влажной салфеткой, что говорит о стойкости продукта :)) Кремовая текстура, на губах ощущается довольно комфортно, чувствуется, что в составе есть увлажняющие компоненты.6. Увлажняющий тоник для сухой кожи лица от EO Laboratorie не подходит моей комбинированной коже, так что будет подарен той, кому он больше подойдет.7. Двухфазная сыворотка-спрей Gliss Kur «Экстремальное восстановление» от Schwarzkopf. Производитель обещает уменьшить ломкость волос до 95%, звучит слишком многообещающе, чтобы быть правдой, но лишнее увлажнение и питание моим волосам точно не помешает.8. The Beauty Team’s May Favourites 
Oh, May. The month that brings us tantalisingly close to the dreamy days of summer… albeit with a little bit of rain thrown into the mix, just to keep us on our toes. Our May favourites have been just as changeable, blending lots of exciting newness in with a couple of dependable, can’t-live-without classics that always pull us through.
With DHA-free tanners, new generation masks, plus the reinvention of an iconic product or two, there’s been some amazing innovation this month – and we can’t wait to share them with you. Here’s what’s been rocking our world…
 

Emma
I’ve well and truly kicked my summer prep into gear this month. The first step in my mission? Achieving a really natural, low maintenance summer glow, and I’ve managed to find some seriously impressive products that are ticking all of the right boxes. Add to that some ultra swishy, soft and smooth hair, and I’m pretty much in beauty nirvana with my May favourites.
The New…
Guerlain Terracotta Pause d’Ete Bronzing Powder Duo
I just love limited edition beauty. There’s something so satisfying about owning a limited run of something, especially when it’s inspired by an icon – which just so happens to be exactly what Terracotta Pause d’Ete is!  For summer 2016, Guerlain have transformed their classic Terracotta bronzer with a brand new pattern and a touch of peachy pink blush for added freshness. This beautifully scented, versatile travel companion will see you through summer parties, holidays, the festival season… and beyond!
Hylamide Glow Radiance Booster
Ceryn gave this a thorough run-through last month, and the results were so perfectly golden that I couldn’t resist treating myself. The Hylamide Radiance Booster is the DHA-free self tanner that you never knew you needed (a little more on the DHA debate here), working to give skin the most gradual and natural glow that is the epitome of healthy-looking. I’m not a habitual self tanner – I don’t have the patience for uneven fading – so popping a few drops of this into my normal moisturiser is an ideal fit for me.
… and The Classic
Schwarzkopf BC Bonacure Repair Rescue Treatment Masque
This is my secret weapon for dry and damaged hair. I’ve recommended it countless times, and I’ve yet to hear a dud review. Honestly. The Repair Rescue Treatment Masque came to my aid yet again recently, as around the same time that my skin started to become ultra fragile, so too did my hair. This intensely moisturising treatment transformed the quality of my hair – I could actually run my fingers through the ends again. It’s an all-time favourite.
 

Chelsey
This month I’ve taken a more mature approach to my beauty routine (for a change), focusing on elegant additions that give me an effortless edge without trying too hard. In line with a lot of our lovely customers, this month’s favourites consist of a chic and sophisticated array of the best loved beauty.
The New…
Narciso Rodriguez Narciso Eau de Parfum Spray Poudrée
I don’t know about you, but there isn’t a Narciso fragrance that I haven’t become obsessed with. So when the new Poudree sauntered into HQ, I just knew it had my name written all over it. And, wowzas, I am in awe! Powdery elegance at its finest, there’s something extremely empowering about a sassy scent that begs the question, ‘what are you wearing?’
GIVENCHY Mister Brow Groom – Universal Brow Setter
My brows are my everything, and when they’re not looking their best, I don’t feel my best. Leaving the house at 7:30am, speedy service is what I need, and the new GIVENCHY Mister Brow Groom Universal Brow Setter has answered all of my framing needs. The clue is in the name; its tapered brush grooms and sets my brows in place perfectly. Goodbye scraggly ends, hello more time in the morning.
…And The Classic
DHC Velvet Coat Primer
Primers have always been a bit of a taboo for me… well, that’s until I met the DHC Velvet Skin Coat. I always used to get caught out with flaky areas and un-even texture, but it’s as if this nifty primer has listened to all of concerns and finally provided me with the base that I deserve. Mattifying, moisturising and exceptionally hardworking, its £17 price point is perfect for those looking to try a game-changing primer that actually helps with makeup longevity.
 

Ceryn
May for me was all about discovery. I discovered three products that have completely changed my approach toward beauty and have made my routine easier and far more effective in so many ways. Going in to June my skin is clearer, better protected from the sun and my eyelashes look better than ever!
The New…
NIOD Flavanone Mud 
It’s no secret that I’m a bit of a skincare junkie and usually it’s difficult for me to find a product that’s unlike anything that’s already in my beauty drawers. That was until the NIOD Flavanone Mud turned up! This mask works way harder than your ordinary mud mask, helping purify and decongest skin both instantly and overtime. Now that I have this I’d give up my other masks in a heartbeat!
Bioderma Hydrabio Eau de Soin Anti-UV Mist  SPF30
Applying sunscreen isn’t one of my favourite tasks; it can be messy and pretty tedious and thus I’m always on the lookout for products to make my suncare routine quicker and easier. Queue the Bioderma Hydrabio Eau de Soin Anti-UV Mist SPF30, a product that has not left my handbag ever since its release earlier this month. A rehydrating mist packed with protection, it’s a skincare/suncare hybrid everyone should own.
…And The Classic
Shiseido Eyelash Curlers 
Even though I’ve heard people say time and time again that eyelash curlers make the world of difference I never took action and bought myself a pair. This month that all changed and I treated myself to the Shiseido Eyelash Curlers – and it’s safe to say I am never looking back. Now a staple in my beauty routine, the curlers make my eyes appear more open and completely change the way my makeup look turns out.
 
 
Over to you!

Have you signed up with Toluna?
In addition to being rewarded with cash for taking surveys, Toluna Panel Members also have the opportunity to test products for FREE! If this sounds like something you’d enjoy, then you’ll definitely want to sign up for the Toluna Panel Community.
Once you have completed the quick Toluna registration (note that you’ll need to be sure to click on the link in the confirmation email that is sent), click on the “Explore” tab located in the menu bar across the top of the site and then click on “Test Products”.

Heinäkuun loppuneet Kahdentoista kuukauden roskaprojekti on taas yli puolessavälissä ja koko vuoden määrä taitaa tänäkin vuonna tulla olemaan aikamoinen. Monien muiden kosmetiikkabloggaajien tavoin kun myös minä säästän kaikki tyhjentyneet tuotteet ja käyn ne läpi kuunvaihteessa sekä teen yhteenvedon vuoden lopussa. Testaan toki tuotteita ehkä keskivertokuluttajaa enemmän, mutta roskamäärä on monella muullakin kosmetiikkaa käyttävällä yllättävän suuri - niitä jemmailemalla määrä vaan tulee todellisena esiin! Asuinkaupungissani ei muuten kerätä talouksista erikseen energiajätettä kaatopaikkajätteestä, mikä on pitkään kiukuttanut minua. Vaikkei tämä muovimäärä ole itsessään mikään ekoteko niin pienenä lohdutuksena ainakin se on, että vien ne kerran vuodessa paikkaan, jossa voin lajitella ne!Heinäkuussa tyhjeni 18 tuotetta, joista muutama on holy grail -tuotteitani eli uusi vastaava on jo käytössä! Totutusti eniten loppui taas kasvojen- ja vartalonhoitotuotteita.Lumene Ultra Sensitive Rauhoittava ja kosteuttava naamio tuli joskus LivBoxista, en ehtinyt ostaa tuubia itse ostoslistaltani mutta lisää saatan ostaa! Todella miellyttävä, kosteuttava naamio herkällekin iholle. Emulsiomainen naamio rauhoittaa punoittavaa ihoa ja käytin tätä usein yövoiteen sijaan kun ihoa kiristeli esimerkiksi saunomisen jälkeen.Mossa Cleansing Micellar Water* näkyi tässä postauksessani merkin tuotteista. Tuoksu oli aluksi nenääni vähän tunkkainen (en välitä monista ruusuntuoksuista) mutta tykästyin tähän silti. Ihana aamuputsari!Lancôme Dream Tone Ultimate Dark Spot Corrector oli minulla vaaleimmassa sävyssä 1. Kauniisti ihoa heleyttävä seerumi, joka tasoittaa ihonsävyä. Seerumi lupaa häivyttää maksaläiskiä ja estää uusien syntymistä, kesäaikaan mainio tuote pigmenttimuutoksia torjumaan. Seerumissa on pientä helmiäistä, mikä jättää iholle kauniin hehkun.Clarins Liquid Bronze Self Tanning on kevyesti väriä kasvoille tuova maitomainen tuote, joka on ehdottomasti suosikki-itseruskettavani kasvoille. Tämä sopii myös meille kalpeille eikä lopputulos ole yhden käyttökerran jälkeen liian ilmeinen. Tuote neuvotaan levittämään iholle vanulapulle mutta itse hieron sen ihoon käsin tavallisen kosteusvoiteen tavoin. Vanulappu tuntuu imevän turhan suuren määrän.Hiustuotteita loppui kaksi. Framesi BY Color Protection Hair Spray* -hiuslakka tuntui loputtomalta! 500 ml:n pullo on todellakin riittoisa. Hyvin pitävä lakka, mutta vahva tuoksu alkoi häiritä. En tiedä onko tuoksu tämän sisältämästä amaranttiöljystä vai mistä..Schwarzkopf got2be Powder'ful-hiuspuuteri todellakin tuo volyymia tyveen! Hienojakoinen puuteri tuntuu tahmealta käsissä ja näyttää häviävän hetkessä, mutta hiuksissa se luo runsaasti tekstuuria. Kuivashampoon korvike hiuspuuteri ei ole!Nicole by OPI Wear Something Spar-Kylie oli upea, viileänpinkki glitterlakka. Noin kolmasosa kuivui pulloon joten pois lentää.NYX Powder Blush sävyssä Taupe on se suosittu varjostussävy, jonka ostinkin jo HD Blush -versiona uudelleen. Vain keskeltä ehti tulla pannu esiin mutta ostin tämän niin kauan aikaa sitten, etten viitsi enää käyttää. Puuteri ei enää tunnu samanlaiselta kuin ostaessa.Näytteitä muistin heinäkuussa käyttää vain kaksi, nekin samaa tuotetta. Max Factor Skin Luminizer -meikkivoide oli yllättävän peittävää, nimen perusteella odotin kuultavaa lopputulosta. Voide on todella täyteläistä, voisin kuvitella tämän sopivan myös hyvin kuivalle iholle. Sävy Light Ivory oli minulle vaaleudeltaan sopiva mutta selvästi liian punapohjainen. Sitten vartalotuotteisiin! Gillette Satin Care Sensitive Skin Shave Gel on tosi perus ihokarvojenajogeeli, toimii kyllä. Jämäkästä geelistä tulee täyteläinen vaahto, tykkään kyllä mutta käytän nykyään enemmän tuubeissa tulevia vaihtoehtoja.Compeed Cracked Heel Overnight Cream* on tehokkaasti kovettumat ja muut kuivat kohdat jalkojen ihosta pehmentävä voide. Ehdottomasti yksi parhaista, joita olen kokeillut! Rasvaan jalkani lähes joka päivä, minulla on melkein pakkomielle pitää iho pehmeänä.. Ihoni kuivuu helposti ja ajatus sänkyyn kömpimisestä kuivuuttaan vähänkin karheilla jaloilla inhottaa! Siis se, kun tuntee kuivan ihon lakanaa vasten, hyi! ACO After Sun 24H Moisturising Gel Cream* on kosteuttava, raikastava ja viilentävä geelimäinen voide - koostumus muistuttaa täyteläistä emulsiota. Käytin tätä myös tavallisen vartalovoiteen tapaan, en oikein ole auringonottaja. Tuoksu on ACO:lle ominaisesti mieto, puhdas ja raikas, oikein miellyttävä! Iho jäi hetkeksi aavistuksen tahmeaksi tämän levittämisen jälkeen, mistä kuivaihoisena pidän, ja illalla käytettynä vielä aamullakin iho tuntui hyvin kosteutetulta.Vaseline Intensive Care Spray Moisturizer* on myöskin miedontuoksuinen kosteuttaja kropan iholle. Suihkutettava kosteusvoide on kevyt, nopeasti imeytyvä tuote. Kuivalle iholleni ei aina tarpeeksi kosteuttava, mutta aamukäytössä aivan mahtava! Aamusuihkun jälkeen minulla harvoin on aikaa odotella kosteusvoiteen imeytymistä ihoon. Suihke on nopea käyttää ja nopea imeytymään.Nivea Daily Essential Cleansing Wipes* ovat normaalille iholla suunnattuja puhditusliinoja. Käytin näitä lähes yksinomaan meikkien pyyhkimiseen käsistä meikatessa ja swatchaillessa. Toimivat kyllä siinä! Valitettavasti silmämeikkien poistamiseen en näitä tajunnut kokeilla - huomasin vasta, että liinat lupaavat poistaa myös vedenkestävän ripsivärin! Tuoksu on melko vahva, saippuainen Nivea-tuoksu.Crystal Body Deodorant -mineraalidödösuihketta on loppunut jo niin monta pulloa, että kaikki varmasti tietää tämän olevan luottotuotteeni! En osaa käyttää kivimuodossa olevia versioita ja tämä kätevä spray maksaa iHerbissä muutaman euron. Pitävyyden arvioimiseen en ole paras mahdollinen henkilö koska lähes kaikki deodorantit toimivat minulla. Ei ehkä tehokkain dödö mutta jos alumiinittomat kiinnostaa, kannattaa kokeilla!LV Hoitava Käsivoide* on mahtava peruskäsirasva! Nopeasti imeytyvä, pehmentävä voide on kulkenut laukussani mukana.
